61c60b3c-7c08-11f1-9bc3-ca3196b25ae3	{"pk": 6, "name": "Loop Bot"}	2026-07-10 02:38:06.714807+00	1	f	userstories.userstory:39	{"status": [8, 9], "description": ["## 故事（必填）\\nAs a signed-in user, I want the dashboard to show a stats widget, so I can see key numbers at a glance.\\n\\n## 驗收提示（盡量填，一行一條）\\n- Dashboard renders a standalone StatsWidget component (selector app-stats-widget)\\n- The widget shows three labelled stats: Active users, Open tickets, Deploys today\\n- Component lives at src/app/dashboard/stats-widget/stats-widget.ts\\n\\n## 不要做（防止範圍蔓延）\\n- No backend/API calls — static demo values are fine\\n- Do not change the login page\\n", "---\\nstory: hackdemo#39\\nspec_version: 1\\ngenerated: 2026-07-10T00:00:00Z\\n---\\n# Feature: Dashboard stats widget\\n\\n## Summary\\nAdd a standalone `StatsWidget` Angular component to the dashboard so that a signed-in user can see three key numbers at a glance: Active users, Open tickets, and Deploys today. The widget displays static demo values with no backend or API calls. The login page is not touched.\\n\\n## Acceptance criteria\\n- AC-1: A component file exists at `src/app/dashboard/stats-widget/stats-widget.ts`.\\n- AC-2: The `StatsWidget` component declares the selector `app-stats-widget`.\\n- AC-3: The `StatsWidget` component is a standalone Angular component (`standalone: true` or Angular ≥19 default standalone).\\n- AC-4: The dashboard component template contains exactly one `<app-stats-widget>` element.\\n- AC-5: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text `Active users` and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)\\n- AC-6: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text `Open tickets` and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)\\n- AC-7: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text `Deploys today` and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)\\n- AC-8: All stat values are rendered via Angular template binding (interpolation or property binding), with no use of `innerHTML` or `bypassSecurityTrust*`. (§2)\\n- AC-9: The `StatsWidget` component does not inject `HttpClient` and issues zero HTTP requests when rendered.\\n- AC-10: No files under the login page's directory are modified by this change. (§5)\\n\\n## Applicable constitution clauses\\n§2 (Validate and encode all user input), §3 (Accessibility is not optional), §5 (Keep the demo stub honest)\\n\\n## Out of scope\\n- No backend/API calls — stat values are hardcoded static demo values.\\n- No changes to the login page or the login stub's behavior.\\n- No new routes in `app.routes.ts`; the widget renders inside the existing dashboard.\\n- No live/refreshing data, polling, or real-time updates (inferred).\\n- No user configuration of which stats are shown (inferred).\\n- No authentication or visibility-gating logic beyond what the dashboard already has (inferred).\\n\\n## Open questions\\n- The exact static demo values for Active users, Open tickets, and Deploys today are not specified.\\n- The widget's position/layout within the dashboard page is not specified.\\n- Visual styling requirements (card style, colors, responsiveness) are not specified."], "kanban_order": [1783651039891133, 1783651086679532], "description_html": ["<h2 id=\\"_1\\">故事（必填）</h2>\\n<p>As a signed-in user, I want the dashboard to show a stats widget, so I can see key numbers at a glance.</p>\\n<h2 id=\\"_2\\">驗收提示（盡量填，一行一條）</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Dashboard renders a standalone StatsWidget component (selector app-stats-widget)</li>\\n<li>The widget shows three labelled stats: Active users, Open tickets, Deploys today</li>\\n<li>Component lives at src/app/dashboard/stats-widget/stats-widget.ts</li>\\n</ul>\\n<h2 id=\\"_3\\">不要做（防止範圍蔓延）</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>No backend/API calls — static demo values are fine</li>\\n<li>Do not change the login page</li>\\n</ul>", "<hr>\\n<p>story: hackdemo#39<br>\\nspec_version: 1<br>\\ngenerated: 2026-07-10T00:00:00Z</p>\\n<hr>\\n<h1 id=\\"feature-dashboard-stats-widget\\">Feature: Dashboard stats widget</h1>\\n<h2 id=\\"summary\\">Summary</h2>\\n<p>Add a standalone <code>StatsWidget</code> Angular component to the dashboard so that a signed-in user can see three key numbers at a glance: Active users, Open tickets, and Deploys today. The widget displays static demo values with no backend or API calls. The login page is not touched.</p>\\n<h2 id=\\"acceptance-criteria\\">Acceptance criteria</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>AC-1: A component file exists at <code>src/app/dashboard/stats-widget/stats-widget.ts</code>.</li>\\n<li>AC-2: The <code>StatsWidget</code> component declares the selector <code>app-stats-widget</code>.</li>\\n<li>AC-3: The <code>StatsWidget</code> component is a standalone Angular component (<code>standalone: true</code> or Angular ≥19 default standalone).</li>\\n<li>AC-4: The dashboard component template contains exactly one <code>&lt;app-stats-widget&gt;</code> element.</li>\\n<li>AC-5: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text <code>Active users</code> and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)</li>\\n<li>AC-6: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text <code>Open tickets</code> and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)</li>\\n<li>AC-7: The rendered widget contains a stat with the visible label text <code>Deploys today</code> and an accompanying numeric value. (§3)</li>\\n<li>AC-8: All stat values are rendered via Angular template binding (interpolation or property binding), with no use of <code>innerHTML</code> or <code>bypassSecurityTrust*</code>. (§2)</li>\\n<li>AC-9: The <code>StatsWidget</code> component does not inject <code>HttpClient</code> and issues zero HTTP requests when rendered.</li>\\n<li>AC-10: No files under the login page's directory are modified by this change. (§5)</li>\\n</ul>\\n<h2 id=\\"applicable-constitution-clauses\\">Applicable constitution clauses</h2>\\n<p>§2 (Validate and encode all user input), §3 (Accessibility is not optional), §5 (Keep the demo stub honest)</p>\\n<h2 id=\\"out-of-scope\\">Out of scope</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>No backend/API calls — stat values are hardcoded static demo values.</li>\\n<li>No changes to the login page or the login stub's behavior.</li>\\n<li>No new routes in <code>app.routes.ts</code>; the widget renders inside the existing dashboard.</li>\\n<li>No live/refreshing data, polling, or real-time updates (inferred).</li>\\n<li>No user configuration of which stats are shown (inferred).</li>\\n<li>No authentication or visibility-gating logic beyond what the dashboard already has (inferred).</li>\\n</ul>\\n<h2 id=\\"open-questions\\">Open questions</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>The exact static demo values for Active users, Open tickets, and Deploys today are not specified.</li>\\n<li>The widget's position/layout within the dashboard page is not specified.</li>\\n<li>Visual styling requirements (card style, colors, responsiveness) are not specified.</li>\\n</ul>"]}	\N	{"users": {}, "status": {"8": "Spec Drafting", "9": "Spec Review"}}	@admin spec v1 草稿完成，請審查。	<p><a class="mention" href="http://localhost:9000/profile/admin" title="admin">@admin</a> spec v1 草稿完成，請審查。</p>	\N	\N	f	\N	\N	1	{"status": ["Spec Drafting", "Spec Review"], "kanban_order": [1783651039891133, 1783651086679532], "description_diff": [null, "<del style=\\"background:#ffe6e6;\\">## 故事（必填）<br />As a signed-in user, I want the dashboard to show a stats widget, so I can see key numbers at a glance.<br /><br />## 驗收提示（盡量填，一行一條）<br />- Dashboard renders a standalone </del><ins style=\\"background:#e6ffe6;\\">---<br />story: hackdemo#39<br />spec_version: 1<br />generated: 2026-07-10T00:00:00Z<br />---<br /># Feature: Dashboard stats widget<br /><br />## Summary<br />Add a standalone `StatsWidget` Angular component to the dashboard so that a signed-in user can see three key numbers at a glance: Active users, Open tickets, and Deploys today. The widget displays static demo values with no backend or API calls. The login page is not touched.<br /><br />## Acceptanc